1
00:00:45,045 --> 00:00:47,131
I'm going to try to understand
irrational numbers.

2
00:00:49,508 --> 00:00:50,509
Did he mean me?

3
00:00:50,593 --> 00:00:51,427
But why?

4
00:00:52,470 --> 00:00:53,345
What for?

5
00:00:54,597 --> 00:00:55,431
Why on earth?

6
00:00:55,514 --> 00:00:56,557
What?

7
00:00:56,640 --> 00:00:59,185
CHAPTER 29:
SOMETIMES, THE TRUTH CAN BE DANGEROUS

8
00:01:00,853 --> 00:01:02,646
Um, why…

9
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:08,444
Why would Pythagoras
have killed his student?

10
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:12,406
Isn't it obvious?

11
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:17,495
He couldn't bear to see
his world collapse.

12
00:01:19,872 --> 00:01:23,000
5TH CENTURY BC

13
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:27,922
What is the matter?

14
00:01:29,048 --> 00:01:29,924
Master.

15
00:01:30,007 --> 00:01:31,217
PYTHAGOREAN MATH ACADEMY
CROTON, GREECE

16
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,176
By any chance…

17
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:33,093
PYTHAGORAS, DIRECTOR

18
00:01:33,176 --> 00:01:35,095
…have you discovered something new?

19
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:37,765
HIPPASUS, STUDENT

20
00:01:37,848 --> 00:01:39,558
I tried to express the length

21
00:01:40,351 --> 00:01:42,937
of the diagonal of a unit square

22
00:01:43,813 --> 00:01:46,440
as a fraction.

23
00:01:46,524 --> 00:01:49,485
Sure. All numbers can be expressed
as a ratio of integers.

24
00:01:49,568 --> 00:01:51,487
That is the truth
we have always been spreading.

25
00:01:52,029 --> 00:01:52,905
The thing is…

26
00:01:55,324 --> 00:01:57,283
that doesn't seem to hold true.

27
00:01:58,035 --> 00:01:59,036
What did you say?

28
00:01:59,578 --> 00:02:00,663
This number

29
00:02:01,497 --> 00:02:03,749
just cannot be expressed as a fraction.

30
00:02:04,542 --> 00:02:05,584
Wait.

31
00:02:06,502 --> 00:02:07,336
Just a moment.

32
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:11,924
Fine.

33
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:13,676
Prove it.

34
00:02:20,558 --> 00:02:21,684
This is a square.

35
00:02:22,393 --> 00:02:23,310
Please look closely.

36
00:02:31,193 --> 00:02:33,696
It just does not work.

37
00:02:38,909 --> 00:02:40,202
If your theory is valid,

38
00:02:40,786 --> 00:02:44,373
then everything
we hold to be true is false.

39
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:48,627
Have you…

40
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:51,922
shared this with anyone?

41
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:56,218
I have not told anyone yet.

42
00:02:56,302 --> 00:02:58,470
I wanted to tell you first, Master.

43
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:01,473
Good.

44
00:03:02,266 --> 00:03:03,309
That is fortunate.

45
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,104
Hippasus.

46
00:03:10,107 --> 00:03:11,108
Yes?

47
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:12,943
Let us pretend

48
00:03:14,153 --> 00:03:15,446
your proof never existed.

49
00:03:19,158 --> 00:03:20,075
Master.

50
00:03:20,159 --> 00:03:23,412
Sometimes, the truth can be dangerous.

51
00:03:25,998 --> 00:03:27,166
Master!

52
00:03:34,381 --> 00:03:37,718
The existence of irrational numbers
would have threatened the world order.

53
00:03:40,387 --> 00:03:42,848
Gosh. What a math nerd.

54
00:03:42,932 --> 00:03:45,559
Why does he get a gleam in his eye
whenever he goes over math stuff?

55
00:03:45,643 --> 00:03:46,644
It's freaky.

56
00:03:51,023 --> 00:03:52,358
But still…

57
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:57,279
it is kind of attractive.

58
00:04:07,039 --> 00:04:07,873
Are you okay?

59
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,836
Yes, I'm fine.

60
00:04:14,088 --> 00:04:16,339
That's what happens
when you keep daydreaming.

61
00:04:17,091 --> 00:04:17,925
Yes.

62
00:04:18,676 --> 00:04:19,843
So embarrassing.

63
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:22,554
Please, I've seen far worse.

64
00:04:26,141 --> 00:04:28,060
They say suffering embarrassment

65
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:30,020
boosts your creativity.

66
00:04:30,104 --> 00:04:31,355
I see.

67
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:34,817
So you're doing it deliberately?
What more have you got in store?

68
00:04:35,651 --> 00:04:37,903
Why would I share it and lessen the blow?

69
00:04:37,987 --> 00:04:40,114
Fine, work on your creativity.

70
00:04:40,739 --> 00:04:41,824
I'll be rooting for you.

71
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:48,038
EPISODE 9

72
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:49,456
I'm home.

73
00:04:50,082 --> 00:04:52,292
Hit the bathroom
before you do anything else.

74
00:04:53,627 --> 00:04:54,461
No, I'm good.

75
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:57,047
I know you can't go when you're out.

76
00:04:57,131 --> 00:05:00,384
From now on, go take a dump
as soon as you get home.

77
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:03,262
I mean, when nature calls,

78
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:05,389
don't hold it in. Answer it straightaway.

79
00:05:06,181 --> 00:05:08,142
Okay already.

80
00:05:08,225 --> 00:05:09,727
I can take care of myself.

81
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:11,895
Why are you fussing about me pooping?

82
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:14,064
Obviously because
you're not taking good care of yourself!

83
00:05:16,358 --> 00:05:17,609
Fine.

84
00:05:18,444 --> 00:05:19,319
I'm going.

85
00:05:21,447 --> 00:05:24,199
Should I go and see your homeroom teacher?

86
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:26,243
Why?

87
00:05:27,494 --> 00:05:29,872
He carried you all the way to the ER.

88
00:05:29,955 --> 00:05:32,457
I'm both sorry and grateful.

89
00:05:33,042 --> 00:05:34,918
Oh, no. There's no need for that.

90
00:05:35,002 --> 00:05:36,211
I already thanked him.

91
00:05:36,295 --> 00:05:38,255
He's swamped as is. Don't disturb him.

92
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:39,631
Promise me you won't, okay?

93
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:42,051
I guess he's got you good.

94
00:05:42,801 --> 00:05:45,220
But then again,
he's given you all those demerits.

95
00:05:45,721 --> 00:05:47,097
No wonder you're scared stiff of him.

96
00:05:47,181 --> 00:05:49,475
Gosh, he must be quite the hard-ass.

97
00:05:50,308 --> 00:05:51,935
You're in for a tough time.

98
00:05:52,019 --> 00:05:54,605
Well, he's not that bad.

99
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:57,357
He's just a bit blunt.

100
00:05:57,441 --> 00:06:01,236
He's a bit on the prickly side,

101
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,405
but he's not a bad guy…

102
00:06:03,489 --> 00:06:05,949
Sometimes he can be childish and immature,

103
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:07,659
but he's not a bad guy at heart.

104
00:06:07,743 --> 00:06:08,827
…at heart.

105
00:06:29,973 --> 00:06:31,016
I get it now.

106
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:34,728
They say smart people
are masters of manipulation.

107
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:36,897
There we have it.

108
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:39,191
I'm being manipulated.

109
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:41,235
Just like Mr. Yoon.

110
00:06:42,194 --> 00:06:44,029
When you're scolded
and yelled at ten times,

111
00:06:44,113 --> 00:06:45,656
one kind comment will make you go,

112
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:48,117
"Wait, maybe he's not so bad after all."

113
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,868
Yes, that's exactly it.

114
00:06:54,331 --> 00:06:56,959
Seriously though,
he's been so mean to me all this time.

115
00:06:57,042 --> 00:07:00,045
The jerk says he'd try to understand me,
then my heart skips a beat?

116
00:07:00,129 --> 00:07:01,130
How ridiculous!

117
00:07:06,176 --> 00:07:08,428
Pull yourself together, Eui-ju.

118
00:07:08,512 --> 00:07:11,098
Starting tomorrow, don't even look at him.

119
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:18,730
CHAPTER 30:
SOMEONE I SHOULDN'T AND CAN'T LIKE

120
00:07:22,192 --> 00:07:23,026
Hey, did you see?

121
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,445
That thing I sent in our group chat.

122
00:07:25,529 --> 00:07:27,656
About Professor Na Deul-i at Princeton

123
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:30,742
becoming the first Korean
to be awarded the Fields Medal.

124
00:07:30,826 --> 00:07:33,287
What about it? Do you know her?

125
00:07:33,996 --> 00:07:34,872
No, I don't.

126
00:07:35,497 --> 00:07:36,874
But Woo-su does.

127
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,836
She was on his Olympiad team
back in middle school.

128
00:07:42,045 --> 00:07:43,046
Really?

129
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:44,506
Aren't you jealous?

130
00:07:45,174 --> 00:07:47,301
Don't you think that should have been you?

131
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,764
If only you hadn't dropped out
of the Olympiad.

132
00:07:53,891 --> 00:07:55,851
If you had only studied abroad--

133
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:57,811
What's wrong?

134
00:07:58,437 --> 00:08:00,022
I thought he was going places.

135
00:08:00,731 --> 00:08:01,940
I had no idea he'd end up here,

136
00:08:02,024 --> 00:08:04,568
bickering with math idiots like you
over toast with me.

137
00:08:05,694 --> 00:08:07,321
I'm talking about my friend Woo-su.

138
00:08:07,905 --> 00:08:09,948
Woo-su, my freaking genius buddy.

139
00:08:12,075 --> 00:08:14,036
Whatever. Forget it.

140
00:08:14,536 --> 00:08:16,872
-He could've won the Fields Medal and--
-Hey.

141
00:08:17,456 --> 00:08:18,498
Give it a rest.

142
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:21,835
What's so special about some dumb medal?

143
00:08:24,922 --> 00:08:25,797
Hey.

144
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:28,342
Do you even know what the Fields Medal is?

145
00:08:29,593 --> 00:08:30,427
Of course, I do.

146
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:33,304
Then tell me who the first recipient was.

147
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:39,561
David Copperfield.

148
00:08:39,645 --> 00:08:40,687
Forget it.

149
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:43,523
Why should I bother
talking to someone so ignorant?

150
00:08:44,483 --> 00:08:45,400
Anyhow, Woo-su, you're…

151
00:08:48,153 --> 00:08:49,529
I won't bother with you either.

152
00:08:50,239 --> 00:08:51,406
Enjoy your toast.

153
00:08:59,790 --> 00:09:01,291
When is he going to come out?

154
00:09:03,335 --> 00:09:05,045
It's normally about now.

155
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:07,089
Do I have everything I need?

156
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:08,715
Did I bring all my textbooks?

157
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:10,634
I'd better wear my puffer jacket.

158
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:12,094
Why isn't he here already?

159
00:09:12,177 --> 00:09:13,387
We're going to be late.

160
00:09:14,638 --> 00:09:15,806
Da-ju, get a move on.

161
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:17,224
Woo-su left an hour ago.

162
00:09:17,307 --> 00:09:19,142
Jeez, he's a real pain in the neck.

163
00:09:19,226 --> 00:09:20,644
-What on earth?
-What time is it?

164
00:09:20,727 --> 00:09:22,145
We're late for sure.

165
00:09:22,229 --> 00:09:23,897
Jeez, he's always like this.

166
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:25,941
Isn't that Eui-ju?

167
00:09:27,025 --> 00:09:28,318
Eui-ju?

168
00:09:28,402 --> 00:09:29,403
She'll be late too.

169
00:09:34,533 --> 00:09:37,077
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

170
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,537
Good morning.

171
00:09:39,538 --> 00:09:42,332
Why is he doing that with his hair?

172
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:43,834
Let's get started.

173
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,753
Why has he pushed his sleeves up?

174
00:09:49,464 --> 00:09:51,216
Why are his fingers so long?

175
00:10:02,853 --> 00:10:05,814
Why is he drinking water like that?

176
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,653
The way he's twiddling his pen…

177
00:10:14,823 --> 00:10:15,699
It's so…

178
00:10:17,576 --> 00:10:18,410
It's so…

179
00:10:19,202 --> 00:10:20,245
So obnoxious.

180
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:25,709
What is it you want to tell me?

181
00:10:26,376 --> 00:10:27,461
Let's take a seat here.

182
00:10:32,758 --> 00:10:33,800
Go-ya.

183
00:10:33,884 --> 00:10:38,180
Fangirling used to be my only joy in life.

184
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:39,723
I know.

185
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:44,728
Of course, many were fictional characters,

186
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:46,813
but my love for them

187
00:10:46,897 --> 00:10:48,732
was always genuine.

188
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:51,735
Thinking about those characters

189
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:53,779
gave me the strength to carry on.

190
00:10:54,738 --> 00:10:55,864
But now…

191
00:10:56,615 --> 00:10:58,867
The fact he keeps cropping up in my mind…

192
00:11:00,827 --> 00:11:01,828
It makes me mad.

193
00:11:02,746 --> 00:11:04,623
The thing is…

194
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:07,000
I don't want to think about him.

195
00:11:07,084 --> 00:11:09,836
I shouldn't think about him,

196
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:11,338
but I can't help myself.

197
00:11:13,215 --> 00:11:14,257
You're in denial.

198
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:16,843
In denial?

199
00:11:16,927 --> 00:11:18,428
You're always like this.

200
00:11:18,512 --> 00:11:21,765
You watch countless videos of some idol
while claiming not to be a fan

201
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:25,060
or save a gazillion photos
of the lead actor in some series

202
00:11:25,143 --> 00:11:26,812
but say you only watch the show
for his acting.

203
00:11:28,063 --> 00:11:30,232
Do I really?

204
00:11:30,315 --> 00:11:31,942
Yes, you do.

205
00:11:32,776 --> 00:11:35,821
Even when you're into someone,
you don't want to admit it.

206
00:11:35,904 --> 00:11:38,532
No matter how much you deny it,
you're already into him.

207
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:40,075
No way.

208
00:11:41,368 --> 00:11:42,828
That can't be it.

209
00:11:43,412 --> 00:11:46,123
No. I shouldn't even like him,

210
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:47,874
and I just can't.

211
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:49,793
Why not?

212
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:50,752
Huh?

213
00:11:52,379 --> 00:11:54,798
Why can't you like Mr. Jung?

214
00:11:59,469 --> 00:12:00,303
What?

215
00:12:01,471 --> 00:12:03,849
Why are you in denial about liking him?

216
00:12:05,934 --> 00:12:06,810
Oh…

217
00:12:09,438 --> 00:12:10,772
It's not like that.

218
00:12:10,856 --> 00:12:11,690
No.

219
00:12:12,983 --> 00:12:14,067
-Shall we get going?
-What?

220
00:12:14,151 --> 00:12:15,694
You solved my problem. Let's go.

221
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:17,571
-Huh?
-Let's go. I'm good now.

222
00:12:19,114 --> 00:12:20,240
Oh. Hey, Jenny.

223
00:12:20,323 --> 00:12:21,366
Where are you going?

224
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:22,784
Oh, the teachers' office.

225
00:12:22,868 --> 00:12:25,704
I'm gonna apply for a field trip.

226
00:12:25,787 --> 00:12:27,622
I'm so jealous. Where are you going to go?

227
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:30,542
I'll dress up in hanbok
and visit the Gyeongbokgung Palace.

228
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:31,877
And then… The market.

229
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,129
I'm going to try gimbap
and tteokbokki there.

230
00:12:34,212 --> 00:12:37,215
Then on to Hongdae before heading
to the Han River to eat ramyeon.

231
00:12:37,299 --> 00:12:38,800
Finally, I'll check out
Namsan Seoul Tower.

232
00:12:41,219 --> 00:12:43,430
Are you sure you have the energy

233
00:12:43,513 --> 00:12:44,723
to do all that in one day?

234
00:12:44,806 --> 00:12:46,475
-Sure.
-But Jenny,

235
00:12:46,558 --> 00:12:48,768
you do know you have to write a report
when you get back, right?

236
00:12:48,852 --> 00:12:50,645
Of course.

237
00:12:50,729 --> 00:12:53,482
"I learned a lot about Korean culture."

238
00:12:53,565 --> 00:12:55,025
That should cover it, no?

239
00:12:55,609 --> 00:12:56,568
Bye!

240
00:12:58,528 --> 00:13:01,781
I guess no one has shown her
the report form yet.

241
00:13:02,365 --> 00:13:04,242
Leave her be. She looks so happy.

242
00:13:04,326 --> 00:13:05,744
I guess. Goodness.

243
00:13:05,827 --> 00:13:08,538
THE DANCING CARNATION
NOTABLE WORK "MY MOTHER" BY YOON DONG-JU

244
00:13:22,928 --> 00:13:23,762
Wow.

245
00:13:24,262 --> 00:13:25,764
Are you reading that again?

246
00:13:26,389 --> 00:13:28,266
You must have it memorized by now.

247
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:29,184
Of course.

248
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:32,187
"On the face of the woman
who no longer smiles,

249
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:34,814
a single flower in full bloom emerged."

250
00:13:35,524 --> 00:13:39,069
Maybe Dong-ju's mother is not smiling
because she passed away.

251
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:42,489
"And another small flower
that doesn't answer."

252
00:13:42,572 --> 00:13:45,742
The small flower
is probably Dong-ju himself.

253
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,788
Why didn't he answer
when his mother called him?

254
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,040
Why didn't he look at her?

255
00:13:52,958 --> 00:13:54,793
Probably out of resentment, right?

256
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:58,421
He must regret that so much now.

257
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:01,049
You know what?

258
00:14:01,633 --> 00:14:03,385
If you'd put this much effort
into your studies,

259
00:14:03,468 --> 00:14:04,844
you'd be crushing Korean Literature.

260
00:14:07,097 --> 00:14:08,682
How are you getting on with your poem?

261
00:14:09,683 --> 00:14:10,517
Well…

262
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:14,688
Hey.

263
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:15,772
It's Mr. Yoon.

264
00:14:19,276 --> 00:14:20,694
Hello.

265
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:06,781
Hey.

266
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:08,658
Why didn't you come over and say hi?

267
00:15:11,036 --> 00:15:12,871
You two have gotten really close.

268
00:15:14,497 --> 00:15:16,124
Not at all.

269
00:15:16,207 --> 00:15:17,709
He just gave me feedback on my poem.

270
00:15:28,553 --> 00:15:30,513
I shouldn't even like him,

271
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:32,349
and I just can't.

272
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:43,443
That's what happens
when you keep daydreaming.

273
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,571
His voice

274
00:15:47,405 --> 00:15:50,325
was definitely full of concern.

275
00:15:54,788 --> 00:15:56,623
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 6

276
00:15:59,709 --> 00:16:02,462
You're the future head
of the family company,

277
00:16:03,213 --> 00:16:04,589
and you're carrying on

278
00:16:05,674 --> 00:16:07,592
with some guy?

279
00:16:07,676 --> 00:16:09,511
Are you out of your mind?

280
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:11,888
Who told you that? Who would dare…

281
00:16:16,935 --> 00:16:18,144
It was me, Si-on.

282
00:16:20,271 --> 00:16:21,272
I did it for you.

283
00:16:21,856 --> 00:16:22,691
You?

284
00:16:24,818 --> 00:16:25,860
So you joined the company

285
00:16:25,944 --> 00:16:29,030
to get close to my mom and rat me out
about my relationship with Yoon?

286
00:16:29,948 --> 00:16:31,908
I was only looking out for your future.

287
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:35,036
You're destined for great things.

288
00:16:36,579 --> 00:16:38,415
You can't afford to set tongues wagging.

289
00:16:39,457 --> 00:16:40,750
Don't make me laugh.

290
00:16:41,418 --> 00:16:44,379
You think if you break us up,
he'll run into your arms?

291
00:16:44,462 --> 00:16:45,547
He was the first person

292
00:16:46,673 --> 00:16:47,924
to laugh at my jokes.

293
00:16:48,007 --> 00:16:49,217
You've got to be kidding me.

294
00:16:49,843 --> 00:16:52,345
He laughed at my jokes.

295
00:16:53,096 --> 00:16:55,098
To spare your feelings, no doubt.
He's kind that way.

296
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:57,225
No, that's not it.

297
00:16:57,851 --> 00:16:58,852
You have no idea

298
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:01,730
about the way he looks at me.

299
00:17:01,813 --> 00:17:04,398
He doesn't look at anyone else that way.

300
00:17:04,482 --> 00:17:05,525
-It's the same.
-No.

301
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:06,568
-Exactly the same.
-No…

302
00:17:08,486 --> 00:17:10,905
You're welcome
to take your anger out on me.

303
00:17:10,989 --> 00:17:12,781
But if you touch him, I won't let it go.

304
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,622
-No, I won't let you pass.
-Get out of my way.

305
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:21,458
No. Never…

306
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:24,335
-Mr. Kim!
-Yes, ma'am.

307
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:29,632
Lock him up until that Choi Yoon

308
00:17:29,716 --> 00:17:31,885
or whatever his name is dealt with.

309
00:17:35,805 --> 00:17:37,682
Let go. Let go of me!

310
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:46,191
Get him!

311
00:18:51,631 --> 00:18:52,465
Are you okay?

312
00:18:53,049 --> 00:18:55,385
What did I tell you
about wandering off alone, Yoon?

313
00:18:56,803 --> 00:18:57,846
Are you hurt?

314
00:19:06,563 --> 00:19:07,522
Let's go.

315
00:19:19,492 --> 00:19:21,494
Shoot, what was that about?

316
00:19:23,538 --> 00:19:25,582
Why did Yoon turn into a self-insert?

317
00:19:25,665 --> 00:19:27,000
Why did I replace Mr. Yoon?

318
00:19:28,376 --> 00:19:30,503
Why was I on fire there?
Everything was so vivid.

319
00:19:32,046 --> 00:19:33,047
No way. Surely not…

320
00:19:41,014 --> 00:19:44,309
TOPOLOGY OF ALGEBRAIC CURVES AND SURFACES

321
00:19:50,064 --> 00:19:51,649
HEY, IT'S BEEN A WHILE

322
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:53,735
I'M BACK IN KOREA
CAN WE MEET UP?

323
00:19:58,948 --> 00:20:00,450
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

324
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:18,718
I'll try that.

325
00:20:24,766 --> 00:20:25,683
Go-ya.

326
00:20:29,687 --> 00:20:30,730
We need to talk.

327
00:20:38,696 --> 00:20:39,572
What was that?

328
00:20:40,323 --> 00:20:42,116
Oh, well,

329
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:45,370
I told Mr. Yoon I was having difficulty
coming up with a title.

330
00:20:45,453 --> 00:20:48,539
He suggested using the first image
that came to mind when I read my poem,

331
00:20:48,623 --> 00:20:51,209
or the word repeated the most in it.

332
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:54,462
So I tried it,
and I wanted his take on my ideas.

333
00:20:54,545 --> 00:20:55,964
Why did you go by yourself?

334
00:20:56,047 --> 00:20:57,256
You could've taken me along.

335
00:20:58,424 --> 00:21:00,510
I did consider that.

336
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:02,845
But it was no big deal,
so I went to see him by myself.

337
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,098
"No big deal"?

338
00:21:06,349 --> 00:21:09,686
I'm so nervous around Dong-ju
that I can't even say hi to him.

339
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:13,022
But for you, laughing and chatting
with him is no big deal?

340
00:21:16,943 --> 00:21:18,361
Well, the thing is…

341
00:21:18,861 --> 00:21:19,862
Tell me the truth.

342
00:21:20,822 --> 00:21:22,365
The guy you like isn't Mr. Jung, is it?

343
00:21:23,199 --> 00:21:24,450
You like Dong-ju, don't you?

344
00:21:26,077 --> 00:21:27,161
What are you talking about?

345
00:21:27,245 --> 00:21:28,454
I'm right, aren't I?

346
00:21:28,538 --> 00:21:30,581
Otherwise, why would you go see him alone?

347
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:32,375
Why are you in denial?

348
00:21:35,253 --> 00:21:36,504
Wait.

349
00:21:36,587 --> 00:21:38,756
It's not Mr. Yoon.

350
00:21:44,345 --> 00:21:47,724
If it's not him,
why can't you tell me who it is?

351
00:21:47,807 --> 00:21:50,351
You're acting so weird right now.

352
00:21:54,063 --> 00:21:55,106
Don't you trust me?

353
00:21:56,649 --> 00:21:57,483
What?

354
00:21:57,567 --> 00:22:01,029
I told you it's not what you think.
Do you have to keep going on about it?

355
00:22:01,654 --> 00:22:03,656
Have I ever lied to you?

356
00:22:07,368 --> 00:22:08,327
Fine.

357
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:10,079
I guess you're right.

358
00:22:10,163 --> 00:22:13,624
Maybe I'm so blinded by love
that I can't trust an innocent friend.

359
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:23,092
Shall I give it a go?

360
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:25,136
-You think I can do it?
-Shall I do it, then?

361
00:22:25,219 --> 00:22:26,095
Did you get cookies?

362
00:22:26,179 --> 00:22:27,221
Leave me alone.

363
00:22:35,938 --> 00:22:36,773
Hey.

364
00:22:37,607 --> 00:22:38,566
What's up with her?

365
00:22:43,071 --> 00:22:44,572
-You think they argued?
-No doubt.

366
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:45,656
They argued for sure.

367
00:23:08,346 --> 00:23:10,389
She'll get over it soon, right?

368
00:23:28,116 --> 00:23:33,204
CHAPTER 31:
EVERYONE HAS A SPECIAL SOMEONE

369
00:23:48,469 --> 00:23:49,554
Wait.

370
00:23:50,179 --> 00:23:51,097
What the heck?

371
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:54,475
Mr. Jung just left.

372
00:23:54,559 --> 00:23:56,018
So why am I waiting for Mr. Ga?

373
00:23:58,604 --> 00:23:59,564
No way.

374
00:24:00,148 --> 00:24:03,025
Just looking at his face makes me sad.

375
00:24:03,109 --> 00:24:03,943
Are you okay?

376
00:24:08,865 --> 00:24:10,032
No way.

377
00:24:27,967 --> 00:24:28,801
Love is…

378
00:24:28,885 --> 00:24:30,386
like the first snow.

379
00:24:30,469 --> 00:24:31,429
Love at first sight.

380
00:24:31,929 --> 00:24:33,598
When you see them,

381
00:24:33,681 --> 00:24:36,392
you know that person is meant for you.

382
00:24:37,393 --> 00:24:39,020
That's how it is, kiddo.

383
00:24:42,190 --> 00:24:43,566
MINI MOCK EXAMINATION 7

384
00:24:47,945 --> 00:24:49,947
My first snow

385
00:24:50,031 --> 00:24:52,158
isn't Mr. Jung but Mr. Ga?

386
00:24:55,161 --> 00:24:56,245
What am I going to do?

387
00:24:57,788 --> 00:25:00,958
What am I going to do?

388
00:25:08,049 --> 00:25:09,508
Your cafe mocha is ready.

389
00:25:11,594 --> 00:25:13,179
Thanks. Enjoy your drink.

390
00:25:13,262 --> 00:25:14,889
Thank you.

391
00:25:33,991 --> 00:25:34,867
What the heck?

392
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:37,203
What's he doing here?

393
00:25:39,705 --> 00:25:41,040
Why didn't I see him earlier?

394
00:25:41,123 --> 00:25:43,626
When I ordered this earlier…

395
00:25:43,709 --> 00:25:45,378
At the counter…

396
00:25:47,046 --> 00:25:48,172
I can't believe this.

397
00:25:49,924 --> 00:25:53,344
Wait, did he see me
and come in on purpose?

398
00:25:53,427 --> 00:25:54,387
My goodness.

399
00:25:55,429 --> 00:25:56,305
Or maybe not.

400
00:25:57,390 --> 00:25:59,141
Is this what they call fate?

401
00:26:03,145 --> 00:26:04,105
Huh?

402
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:07,733
Cafe mocha?

403
00:26:13,406 --> 00:26:14,573
It doesn't suit him at all.

404
00:26:15,491 --> 00:26:17,326
He's got so much whipped cream on it.

405
00:26:18,077 --> 00:26:20,871
What the heck? He has it just like I do.

406
00:26:21,706 --> 00:26:22,748
What is he playing at?

407
00:26:27,128 --> 00:26:28,587
Who is he waving at?

408
00:26:38,889 --> 00:26:40,016
Long time no see.

409
00:26:40,099 --> 00:26:42,101
I've missed you so much.

410
00:26:45,271 --> 00:26:47,898
Until then,
I didn't understand my own feelings.

411
00:26:48,816 --> 00:26:49,775
But in that moment,

412
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:52,445
everything became crystal clear.

413
00:26:56,032 --> 00:26:59,410
My heart had been running wild,
without direction or plan,

414
00:27:00,036 --> 00:27:01,203
and I finally understood it.

415
00:27:03,247 --> 00:27:04,790
Everyone…

416
00:27:06,375 --> 00:27:07,793
has a special someone

417
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:11,547
who makes their heart sink at least once.

418
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:21,700
Subtitle: Paul Carver
